'''Osangangan Obamakin''' was the 2nd [[Ooni of Ife]], a paramount traditional ruler of [[Ile Ife]], the ancestral home of the [[Yoruba people|Yorubas]]. He succeeded Ooni [[Oduduwa]] and was succeeded by his son, [[Ooni Ogun]].<Ref>{{cite book |last=Dayo|first= Ologundudu|date=2008 |title=The cradle of Yoruba culture|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Vn8uAQAAIAAJ&q=Ooni+Ojigidiri&dq=Ooni+Ojigidiri&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CB0Q6AEwBGoVChMIvMCQ5aKCxwIVjO0UCh0HRAxX|location= Nigeria|publisher=Centre for spoken words |page=206 |isbn=0615220630 |access-date=July 30, 2015}}</ref>

